  "local_port": 39924,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What do you use a social network for?",
  "response": "People use social networks for a variety of purposes, including:\n\n1. **Staying Connected**:  \n   - Communicating with friends, family, and colleagues through messaging, comments, or video calls.  \n   - Sharing life updates, photos, or milestones (e.g., birthdays, travel, events).\n\n2. **Professional Networking**:  \n   - Building career connections (e.g., LinkedIn for job hunting or industry insights).  \n   - Showcasing professional portfolios or skills.\n\n3. **Content Consumption & Entertainment**:  \n   - Watching videos, memes, or live streams.  \n   - Following celebrities, influencers, or content creators.\n\n4. **News & Information**:  \n   - Accessing real-time news, trends, or educational content.  \n   - Participating in discussions about current events or niche topics.\n\n5. **Community Engagement**:  \n   - Joining groups, forums, or hashtag movements around shared interests (e.g., hobbies, activism, fandoms).  \n   - Supporting social causes or fundraising campaigns.\n\n6. **Marketing & Business**:  \n   - Promoting products/services via ads or influencer partnerships.  \n   - Engaging customers through reviews, polls, or direct messaging.\n\n7. **Creativity & Self-Expression**:  \n   - Sharing art, writing, music, or other creative projects.  \n   - Using platforms like TikTok or Instagram Reels for short-form content.\n\n8. **Learning & Skill Development**:  \n   - Taking online courses, attending webinars, or following educational pages.  \n\n9. **Shopping & Commerce**:  \n   - Discovering/buying products via integrated shops (e.g., Facebook Marketplace, Instagram Shops).  \n\n10. **Dating & Relationships**:  \n    - Using apps like Facebook Dating or Bumble to meet new people.  \n\nWhile I, as an AI, don\u2019t use social networks, these are common human uses! \ud83c\udfaf",
